aVScientists measured the electrical activity from the brain
p42
aVas students confronted an error.
p43
aVOn the left, you see the fixed-mindset students.
p44
aVThere's hardly any activity.
p45
aVThey run from the error.
p46
aVThey don't engage with it.
p47
aVBut on the right, you have the students with the growth mindset,
p48
aVthe idea that abilities can be developed.
p49
aVThey engage deeply.
p50
aVTheir brain is on fire with yet.
p51
aVThey engage deeply.
p52
aVThey process the error.
p53
aVThey learn from it and they correct it.
